	(639,3,'2017-07-05 18:51:02','2017-07-05 15:51:02','<p>I have volunteered with RAHU since 2011 and I have seen it grow  as evidenced through the different events, activities and set strategies in RAHU, I can truly say; I have had an amazing experience working with it and it has partly made me who I am today.</p><p>Through RAHU’s Peer Educators Academy that kicked off earlier in January 2014, I got to learn a lot from the different mentors who set the youth development strategies high hence benefiting much more to what was expected.</p><p> RAHU’s out reaches have also been a great deal to me and actually an amazing experience because they have groomed me into someone who can speak out to a large crowd with full confidence, which was not the case in the days before I joined RAHU, on that note I credit RAHU for that.</p><p>And then came the camp, being among those who tasted RAHU’s first sleep away camp in a period of six nights and five days introductory and learning sessions, I can gladly say everything came out successful through a lot of involvement and participation amongst campers, partners and the inspirational speakers who were part of the main drivers of the camp.</p><p>It was such another new amazing experience and therefore congratulate RAHU upon that and also on how far it has reached.</p>','Never Been The Same: Juliana Namata','','inherit','closed','closed','','298-autosave-v1','','','2017-07-05 18:51:02','2017-07-05 15:51:02','',298,'http://localhost/rahu/298-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
